---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Terms of Service — Kovira">
  <div class="relative z-5 flex-1 flex flex-col items-center px-6 py-12 max-w-[640px] mx-auto w-full max-[768px]:px-5 max-[768px]:py-8 overflow-y-auto">
    
    <h1 class="text-[clamp(24px,_3vw,_36px)] font-extrabold leading-[1.2] tracking-[-0.025em] mb-2 text-center text-white">
      <span class="reveal-wrapper">
        <span class="reveal-text delay-1">Terms of Service</span>
      </span>
    </h1>
    
    <p class="text-[11px] text-white/50 text-center mb-10 animate-fade-in delay-2">
      Last updated: June 22, 2026
    </p>

    <div class="w-full flex flex-col gap-6 text-left text-white/60 text-xs leading-relaxed animate-fade-in delay-3">
      
      <section class="flex flex-col gap-2 pb-6 border-b border-white/10">
        <h2 class="text-xs font-bold text-white uppercase tracking-wider">1. Agreement to Terms</h2>
        <p>
          By accessing or using Kovira, you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service and all applicable laws and regulations. If you do not agree with any of these terms, you are prohibited from using or accessing this site.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="flex flex-col gap-2 pb-6 border-b border-white/10">
        <h2 class="text-xs font-bold text-white uppercase tracking-wider">2. Use License</h2>
        <p>
          Permission is granted to temporarily use Kovira's platform for personal or commercial form construction and data gathering. Under this license, you may not modify or copy our source code, use the materials for any public display without attribution, or attempt to decompile any software contained on the platform.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="flex flex-col gap-2 pb-6 border-b border-white/10">
        <h2 class="text-xs font-bold text-white uppercase tracking-wider">3. User Data and Forms</h2>
        <p>
          You retain all ownership rights to the contents and designs of the forms you build and the submissions you collect. However, you are solely responsible for ensuring that your forms comply with data collection regulations (such as GDPR, CCPA, etc.) in your jurisdiction.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="flex flex-col gap-2 pb-6 border-b border-white/10">
        <h2 class="text-xs font-bold text-white uppercase tracking-wider">4. Prohibited Content</h2>
        <p>
          You agree not to use Kovira to collect sensitive credentials, passwords, credit card numbers (outside of supported payment integrations), or any content that is illegal, defamatory, or violates third-party intellectual property.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="flex flex-col gap-2 pb-4">
        <h2 class="text-xs font-bold text-white uppercase tracking-wider">5. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
        <p>
          Kovira is provided "as is". We make no warranties, expressed or implied, and hereby disclaim and negate all other warranties including, without limitation, implied warranties or conditions of merchantability or fitness for a particular purpose.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="pt-6 border-t border-white/10">
        <p class="text-[11px] text-white/50">
          If you have questions about these terms, please contact us at <a href="mailto:legal@kovira.dev" class="text-white hover:underline">legal@kovira.dev</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
